Template: tvtime/norm
Type: select
Choices: NTSC, NTSC-JP, SECAM, PAL, PAL-NC, PAL-M, PAL-N, PAL-60
Description: Select the `Norm' of your television feed?

Template: tvtime/frequencies-menu
Type: select
Choices: Australia, Australia-Optus, Europe, France, Japan-Cable, Japan-Broadcast, NewZealand, Russia, US-Cable, US-Broadcast, Other
Description: Select the default frequency table.

Template: tvtime/frequencies
Type: string
Description: Specify the default frequency table.

Template: tvtime/v4ldevice
Type: string
Default: /dev/video0
Description: Specify your television capture device.

Template: tvtime/ntsccablemode
Type: select
Choices: Standard, IRC, HRC
Default: Standard
Description: Select the NTSC cable standard for your television feed.

Template: tvtime/usevbi
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Do you wish to use VBI?

Template: tvtime/vbidevice
Type: string
Default: /dev/vbi0
Description: Specify the VBI device.

Template: tvtime/deinterlacemethod
Type: select
Choices: Linear, LinearBlend, LineDoubler, Greedy, Greedy2Frame, GreedyH, TomsMoComp, TwoFrame, Vertical, VideoBob, VideoWeave, Weave
Default: GreedyH
Description: Select the deinterlacing method to use.

Template: tvtime/setuid
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Do you wish to make `/usr/bin/tvtime' setuid root?

Template: tvtime/processpriority
Type: string
Default: -19
Description: Specify the process priority for the tvtime binary.
